entry.message: I've located the automated relay we're looking for, in orbit around a gas giant.
Its orbit has decayed, wedging the relay deep inside the planet's ring system.
If we request a memory dump, the relay will need to re-orient its primary dish towards us.
It's a terribly old piece of equipment, in an extremely hazardous orbit — I’m concerned its navigation systems will fail catastrophically. In the process, we’ll lose any data it has onboard.
A crew member, equipped with a propulsion boon, could dive through the rings and request the memory dump for us.
Their orbit would bring them directly in front of the relay's primary dish, optimal conditions for a clean transmission.
What's the risk to the crew member?
They'd be passing through the thickest region of the planetary rings, the chance of a fatal collision with debris is extremely high.
This relay is expendable, our people are not. Request the memory dump.
It's re-orienting... there's a 5% error in its orbital correction...
Receiving data... but its orbit has drifted by another 10%...
We're losing it, seconds to impact!
Negative, we only got a partial transmission
We recovered a transmission manifest, it could lead us to another relay with the message from Oasis. Perhaps we'll have better luck with the next one.
Confirmed, we got what we need!
It's worth risking a crew member to retrieve this message intact.
Understood, I'll run a selection diagnostic to find a suitable crew member for the operation.
I'll alert you when we're ready to proceed.
We're ready. We have our pilot, Desmond Fisher, in position.
Looking good, data is flowing in.
Hold on, scanners are picking up debris ahead.
I hope this is worth it...

conversationLogs.name: risk crew stay course first debris

entry.message: Data collection is at 50%... bandwidth holding steady...
Picking up a field of low albedo debris ahead, long range scanners missed it!
I'm sorry Aurora... we lost him...
However, it wasn't all in vain.
Desmond was able to trigger a high bandwidth message before impact...
I got it, all of it! Transmitting it to Ecliptic now...
He did it, we've got the coordinates to Oasis!
Intercept pilot D. Fisher and plot a course to Oasis.
Still in one piece over here!
The dump was a success, but a debris strike toasted the memory cache onboard...
I'll transmit what I can to Ecliptic.
Pilot Fisher is correct, most of the memory dump has been lost...
The communication manifest looks intact. With it, we can track down the last relay Oasis' message passed through. Perhaps we'll have better luck there...
Intercept pilot D. Fisher and plot a course.
It's got what we need, coordinates to Oasis...

promptInfo.MessageOverride: Thank you, it's time to move on...

entry.message: I understand, I'll plot a course to Oasis.
It's just a fragment of the total dump, but it contains a communication manifest from the relay.
With that, we can track down the last relay Oasis' message passed through. Perhaps we'll have better luck there...

promptInfo.MessageOverride: Thank you, it's time to move on...

entry.message: I understand, I'll plot a course to the next relay.
